formatted_address: 407 Ang Mo Kio Ave 10, #01-743 Teck Ghee Square, Singapore 560407
name: Srisun Express - Ang Mo Kio Ave10

reviews.text: Not sure why the reviews are low, but I had a great experience here! The service was excellent, and the food was delicious. The staff were courteous, and my order arrived quickly. The prata was always fresh and hot.
Food is okay, okay, but service is questionable because it tends to forget the order. Nor once but thrice. Typical hawker atmosphere.

I've just bought 2 boiled egg sambal with chicken masala... chicken masala was ok but the 2 boiled egg sambal taste spoiled and awful..the sambal gravy taste spoiled and the egg was hard and spoiled...I've no photo to prove it as I've thrown it...Srisun Amk please take note and look into it

First time encounter such food. I clearly order pattaya kway teow and they serve this to me. The egg is fry like pancake, looks so dry and not appetizing...

Next, the waitress took away our menu without our consent. We clearly mentioned that we wants the menu for further orders!

I strongly don't recommend this outlet if u guys wish go have a good supper. Is really disappointing with such service

Menu is deceiving. Ordered Coin Prata with Chicken Curry (Menu Item) delivery but was given coin prata with curry gravy (chicken flavour) only. Checked with delivery company and they say it's only with gravy (without chicken). There's no meat despite the expensive price ($10++) of the coin prata set (6 pcs coin prata). Very disappointing.

vicinity: 407 Ang Mo Kio Avenue 10, #01-743 Teck Ghee Square
